main event: A circular disc, 1 1/2 feet in diameter, smaller than the moon, white and red in color, was observed moving up and down and in and out of clouds for about 1 minute.
interesting points: The object was described as a 'fuzzy' object.
The object was moving in an irregular manner, going up and down and in and out of the clouds.
The report was filed with Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's official program for investigating UFO sightings.
The report was from McChord AFB in Washington on January 25, 1956.
The report provided various possible explanations for the sighting, including that it was a balloon or an aircraft, but the final conclusion was 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation'.
